One day, a long long time ago, the sun stopped shining. (Press x to continue)
For 6 months, without the sun's plentiful light and warmth, humanity began to collapse. Crops died, people starved, and war spread throughout the Earth.
The only thing keeping the world from complete darkness was the moon, which shone day and night to protect humanity as much as it possibly could.
One day, a wandering samurai deep in the heart of Japan came across something strange. The moon's bright beam was shining solely on a large tower like a spotlight.
Curious, the warrior approached the tower, and was greeted outside by the Japanese god of the moon, Tsukuyomi.
The god explained that the Sun goddess Amaterasu had been trapped at the top of the tower by her evil sibling Susanoo, god of storms, and that the tower was guarded by slimy monsters.
He then explained the tower existed outside of time and space. This meant that death could be reverted and that the tower would be different every time the warrior tried to climb it. 
Understanding that the only way to free the goddess was to climb the tower, the warrior entered and prepared to make his ascent...
